---
import LayoutV5 from '../../layouts/LayoutV5.astro';
---

<LayoutV5 title="Local Leader | Version 5 Scaffold">
  <main class="mx-auto flex min-h-screen w-full max-w-6xl flex-col justify-center px-6 py-20 sm:px-10">
    <div class="max-w-3xl">
      <p class="mb-4 text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.2em] text-slate-500">Version 5</p>
      <h1 class="text-5xl font-bold tracking-tight text-slate-900 sm:text-6xl">
        Another clean starting point for a <span class="font-serif italic">new concept</span>.
      </h1>
      <p class="mt-6 max-w-2xl text-lg leading-8 text-slate-600">
        Version 5 is ready for a separate reference-led build so each landing page can stay isolated while still using
        the same Local Leader brand system and offer.
      </p>
    </div>

    <section class="mt-14 grid gap-6 md:grid-cols-3">
      <div class="rounded-3xl border border-slate-200 bg-white p-6 shadow-sm">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-slate-900">Conversion target</p>
        <p class="mt-3 text-sm leading-7 text-slate-600">
          Drive strategy-session bookings with proof-led messaging and clear CTA repetition.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="rounded-3xl border border-slate-200 bg-white p-6 shadow-sm">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-slate-900">Build input pack</p>
        <p class="mt-3 text-sm leading-7 text-slate-600">
          Use the organised asset library, the updated brand docs, and the uploaded version-specific screenshots.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="rounded-3xl border border-slate-200 bg-white p-6 shadow-sm">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-slate-900">Build status</p>
        <p class="mt-3 text-sm leading-7 text-slate-600">
          Scaffold only. This route exists so the planning and implementation agents can work independently.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>
</LayoutV5>
